This paper deals with the computational complexity of the weak call-by-value lambda calculus, which is a topic in both logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the measures of time and space complexity, which are important topics in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) to analyze the space overhead of the simulation strategies.
